{"lemma":"رَقِيبٌ","slug":"رَقِيبٌ","root":"ر.ق.ب","root_slug":"ر-ق-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ق-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رَقِيب","root":"رقب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":5},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16313"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"watchman; guard, sentry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"watchman; an inspector, supervisor, even a censor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"watchman; spy, stooge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a certain military rank, usually corresponding to English sergeant"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ra.qiːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16313","headword_ar":"رَقِيبٌ","root":"rqb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A looker, watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiter, in expectation"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of a person or thing]: (S, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqabaA='u","text_ar":"رُقَبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A guarder, guardian, keeper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"preserver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, A, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a guard"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one stationed on an elevated place to keep watch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scout,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of an army: (A, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an observer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~qiybu","text_ar":"الرّقِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appel-lation applied to God; (A, K, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Guardian, Keeper, Watcher,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Observer, from whom nothing is hidden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyn","text_ar":"اَمِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the players at the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, K;) or (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who is intrusted with the supervision of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dariyb","text_ar":"ضَرِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shuffler of the arrows"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (JK, S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the man who stands behind the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuroDap","text_ar":"حُرْضَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the game above mentioned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the meanings of all these explanations are [said to be] the same: pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b5-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The third of the arrows used in the game above mentioned:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, K:) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the seven arrows to which lots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions, appertain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) by some it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~ariybu","text_ar":"الضَّرِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lh, L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Drb","text_ar":"ضرب"},{"kind":"text","text":":) the arrows are ten in number: the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfa*~u","text_ar":"الفَذُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has one notch and one portion; the second,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~awo'amu","text_ar":"التَّوْءَمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has two notches and two portions; the third,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aqiybu","text_ar":"الرَّقِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has three notches and three portions; the fourth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHilosu","text_ar":"الحِلْسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHalisu","text_ar":"الحَلِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has four notches [and four portions]; the fifth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAfisu","text_ar":"النَّافِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has five notches [and five portions]; the sixth,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almusobilu","text_ar":"المُسْبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has six notches [and six portions]; and the seventh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuEal~aY","text_ar":"المُعَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the highest of all, which has seven notches and seven portions: those to which no portions appertain are"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~afiyHu","text_ar":"السَّفِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaniyHu","text_ar":"المَنِيحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwagodu","text_ar":"الوَغْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A_i*aA qasama AlhawaY A^aEo$aAra qalobiY\n                      \n                     \n                        fasahomaAki AlmuEal~aY waAlr~aqiybu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When love divides the tenths of my heart, thy two arrows will be the mo'allà and the rakeeb"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sahomaAni","text_ar":"سَهْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which properly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two arrows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two portions gained by two gaming-arrows,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any two portions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] he means her eyes: and as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mEl~Y","text_ar":"معلّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"has seven portions and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"has three, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"shmAn","text_ar":"سهمان"},{"kind":"text","text":"would gain the whole of his heart. (TA. [See also a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$orN","text_ar":"عُشْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybu Aln~ajomi","text_ar":"رَقِيبُ النَّجْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, that sets with the rising of that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for example, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ikoliylu","text_ar":"الاـِكْلِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": [and the former is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the latter:] when the latter rises at nightfall, the former sets: (S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybN","text_ar":"رَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, which"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watches,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuraAqibu","text_ar":"يُرَاقِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the east, the star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, setting in the west:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any one of the Mansions of the Moon"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of another: (K, TA:) whenever any one of them rises, another [of them] sets: (TA: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAzilu Alqamari","text_ar":"مَنَازِلُ القَمَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nzl","text_ar":"نزل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aqiybu","text_ar":"الرَّقِيبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism, of the stars,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterisms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that were believed to be the givers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rain, that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as it were"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watches another star,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"asterism:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [it was app. applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ikoliylu","text_ar":"الاـِكْلِيلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as being the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the most noted and most welcome of all the Mansions of the Moon, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nawo'N","text_ar":"نَوْءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiyb","text_ar":"رَقِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [also] an appellation applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAnu","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Hyades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the five chief stars of the Hyades;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the brightest star among them,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"α","text_ar":"α","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Taurus"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because a follower thereof: (A:) [and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEay~uwqu","text_ar":"العَيُّوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Capella"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is so called as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAA=tiyka A^awo yaloqaY Alv~uray~aA raqiybuhaA","text_ar":"لَاا=تِيكَ اَوْ يَلْقَى الثُّرَيَّا رَقِيبُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to thee unless their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rqyb","text_ar":"رقيب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meet the Pleiades"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybN","text_ar":"رَقِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (tropical:)  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"successor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"offspring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea$iyrap","text_ar":"عَشِيرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinsfolk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearer"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nearest relations by descent from the same ancestor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niEoma Alr~aqiybu A^anota liA^abiyka wasalafika","text_ar":"نِعْمَ الرَّقِيبُ اَنْتَ لِاَبِيكَ وَسَلَفِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Excellent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most excellent, is the successor;"},{"kind":"text","text":"such art"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou to thy father and thine ancestors"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because the successor is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~abaraAn","text_ar":"الدَّبَرَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alv~uray~aA","text_ar":"الثُّرَيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b8-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"son of a paternal uncle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [App. because two male cousins by the father's side are often rivals, and watchers of each other; the son of a girl's paternal uncle being commonly preferred as her husband.] ―         -b9-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it watched by reason of hatred: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain malignant serpent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raqiybaAtN","text_ar":"رَقِيبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruqubN","text_ar":"رُقُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","Msb","K","JK","A","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}